Node
	Run the js environments
Express
	express is a framework for you to create app
	express is based on node
Npm	
	package/plugins for your app you want to use


###Node
JS runtime environment

Feature:
	1. Asynchronous
	
###Express

1.Framework to build web and api server
2.Middleware
3.Router
4.Error Handler

###Npm
1. Node package manager
2. Manage package
3. Manage Dependencies

install sequencely

### Npm ???
1. Package.json
2. package

###package-lock, yarn-lodk
Lock package versions


### Npm commands
npm inin(create a package.json(config file))
npm install
npm install xxx -D(Save to Dev)
npm install xxx --save(Save to all environments)
npm install xxx -g (Global)
npm install xxx (only will install the package, node v5 above will add --save)
npm install xxx -force(Don't use ) 

### Npx
1. Package runner tool comes with npm
2. Template package that don't wang install golbally

###Yarn
Package manager
与Npm区别: Performs parallel installation

###Yarn commands
yarn init (create a package.json(config file))
yarn install 
yarn add xxx
yarn add xxx -D (Save to Dev)
yarn add xxx -g (Global)

###Workflow
1.Yarn/npm init
	create a package.json
2.yarn/npm install 
	it will create a node_modules folder (where the code is)
	it will upload/create and lock the file
3. yarn/npm add/install
	update package.json
	add the package to node_modules folder
	it will update and lock the package version
	
###Restful API
API Standard

GET (eg: /posts)
GET (eg: /posts/:id)
POST (eg: /posts)
PUT (eg: /posts/:id), larger cuse update while object, create
PATCH (eg: /posts/:id) smaller because update some part of the object
DELETE (eg: /posts/:id)

###PostMan
A tools for you to test your api

{{url}}/api/v1/ 右上角manage Environment下选择不同环境，设置变量，减少重复操作

